description.narrative: The objectives of the Project are to support tourism development in five historically and culturally important cities - Jerash, Karak, Madaba, Salt, Aljoun, - and thereby contribute to local economic development.

condition.narrative: The Borrower shall furnish to the Bank a Mid Term Review Report
each Project Municipality has obtained necessary detailed special building and zoning regulations; and for Ajloun, an enforceablemaster plan with associated land use, zoning & building regulations

title.narrative: Percent of targeted historic buildings in core protected and, where feasible, adaptively reused by the project.

comment.narrative: 10 in Madaba, 2 in Salt, 3 in Karak, and 2 in Ajloun. Only 1 pending completion in Ajloun.

title.narrative: Percent of area of street networks and public spaces in core upgraded under the project.

comment.narrative: Percentage is expected to reach 95% overall, due to delays in Ajloun.

title.narrative: Increase in value of properties in targeted cities

comment.narrative: In addition to positive externalities caused by the project, raise in property values is also due to housing shortage caused bytheinflux of Syrian refugees.

title.narrative: Increased Visitation and Stay in Targeted Cities

comment.narrative: Target missed due to exogenous factors, though the infrastructure delivered through the project will help recovery as the politicalsituation in the region improves.

The geopolitical situation determined by the conflict in Syria continues to impact the average length of stay in Jordan, althoughmuch less than in other countries in the region, showing a relative resilience of the tourism industry in the country, as it cancount on unique assets such as Petra and the Dead Sea.

title.narrative: Number of facilities improved in targeted cities

comment.narrative: The indicator was refined as the number of direct tourism/hospitality and cultural heritage businesses created and/or expanded inproject areas.

title.narrative: Number of Tourism Related Jobs created in target cities

comment.narrative: This target includes direct and indirect jobs created, while the actual progress information reflects only direct jobs, due to lackof data. A complete count also targeting indirect jobs is being carried out through the economic impact assessment currentlyunderway, and will be reported in the ICR.

The number of direct jobs created remains lower than expected as a result of the difficulties faced by the tourism sector due toinstable political situation in the region. The number of indirect jobs created (as is referred in the end target) is beingestimated in an economic impact assessment.
